ubpm(1)                          User Manual                            ubpm(1)

NAME
  ubpm -- usb-based password manager

SYNOPSIS
  ubpm [global options] command [command options] [args...]

DESCRIPTION
  ubpm is an offline password manager designed to run directly from a usb
  drive. it uses aes-256-gcm encryption and argon2id key derivation to ensure
  security of data.

  the vault is stored as a json file in the .ubpm directory on the usb.

INSTALLATION
  build from source:
    $ just build

COMMANDS
  init [-i path]
    initialize a new vault at the specified path. if path is ommited, defaults
    to current directory.

  list [-i path]
    list all entries in the specified vault. if path is ommited, defaults to
    .ubpm/vault.ubpm.json.

  new|add [-i path]
    create a new entry in the specified vault. if path is ommited, defaults to
    .ubpm/vault.ubpm.json.

  show id [-i path] [-j] [flags]
    show the details of a specific entry in the specified vault. -j returns
    specified info in json format. if path is ommited, defaults to
    .ubpm/vault.ubpm.json.

  edit id [-i path] [-tupn]
    edit an entry from the specified vault. -t, -u, -p and -n specify edit scope
    and are short for title, username, password and notes respectively. if path
    is ommited, defaults to .ubpm/vault.ubpm.json.

  rm id [-i path] [--noconfirm]
    delete the specified entry from the specified vault. --noconfirm skips the
    deletion confirmation prompt. if path is ommited, defaults to
    .ubpm/vault.ubpm.json.	

